description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a band 2 Lung Health Screening Clerical Assistant who has previous experience of providing administrative services ideally within a NHS environment. The post holder will be part of a busy but friendly team providing clerical support to the Targeted Lung Health Team. The post will be based at a variety of locations as the project moves through the city. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be joining the team at an exciting time as we re-design our service to deliver a combination of face to face and virtual clinics. Key tasks include answering the telephone, resolving patient queries, booking / changing appointments for clinics, recording referrals, scanning documents, sending electronic tasks, monitoring waiting times, cancelling / adding clinics and patient groups, taking minutes, monitoring patient literature and stationery stock levels, photocopying and booking rooms.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;EMIS and UHNM computer system training will be provided, but experience of patient admin systems is advantageous for this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAlison BainJob titleLead Lung Screening programme NurseEmail addressalison.bain@uhnm.nhs.ukTelephone number01782 671412Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Janina Barnett, project lead Janina.barnett@uhnm.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
